Student: Odile Ornelle Tientcheu
Testing Type: Manual Testing

1. Introduction
This document presents the testing performed on GrabDocs. The goal of this testing was to verify that key features function correctly and identify any limitations affecting functionality.

2. Features Tested
The following features were selected for testing:
File Upload


Messages


Workspace



3. Testing Methodology
Manual testing was used to evaluate the system. Each feature was tested by performing real user actions and comparing expected results with actual outcomes.

4. Test Cases and Results
4.1 File Upload
Objective: Verify file upload functionality


Result: Feature required a paid subscription and could not be fully tested


Status: FAIL



4.2 Messages
Objective: Verify messaging functionality


Result: Messaging feature was restricted and could not be accessed without subscription


Status: FAIL



4.3 Workspace
Objective: Verify workspace management


Result: Workspace feature was accessible and basic functionality worked as expected


Status: PASS



5. Limitations
During testing, some features required a paid subscription to access full functionality. This limited the ability to fully test File Upload and Messages.

6. Conclusion
The Workspace feature functioned as expected. However, File Upload and Messages could not be fully tested due to subscription restrictions. It is recommended that testing be conducted with full system access to validate all features.

